    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In plain English, indemnification is basically a promise to cover the other party's losses. It means if a particular issue arises from your work, you agree to defend them and pay the resulting costs, like legal fees. Think of it as agreeing to take on the risk if something goes wrong because of your contribution to the project. It’s important to check if the language makes you cover unreasonable mistakes.",
